{{Infobox political party | name = Independent Democrats |native_name = Nezávislí demokraté |logo = NEZDEM Logo.jpg |foundation = 2005 |colorcode = transparent |dissolution = 2015<ref>{{cite web|title=Soud pozastavil činnost Železného Nezávislých demokratů|url=http://zpravy.idnes.cz/soud-pozastavil-cinnost-zelezneho-nezavislych-demokratu-pnj-/domaci.aspx?c=A150122_124658_domaci_jpl|website=iDnes.cz|accessdate=1 January 2016}}</ref> |leader = [[Vladimír Železný]] |chairman = |president = |spokesperson = |ideology = [[Populism]] |headquarters = |international = |european = [[Alliance of Independent Democrats in Europe]] |website = |country = the Czech Republic }}
{{Politics of the Czech Republic}}
'''Independent Democrats''' ({{lang-cs|Nezávislí demokraté}} or NEZDEM) was a small [[populism|populist]] [[political party]] in the [[Czech Republic]]. Its founder [[Vladimír Železný]], [[Member of the European Parliament|MEP]], was elected its chairman during the party's convention on 6–7 August 2005. It advocates strict [[immigration]] policies, the abolition of the [[Senate of the Czech Republic|Senate]], and review of the country's relationship with the [[European Union]].
