The '''[[Russian language]] in [[Belarus]]''' is one of the two [[official language]]s (the other being [[Belarusian language|Belarusian]]). Being dominant in the media, education and other areas of public life, Russian is ''de facto'' the main language of the country.
==After 1995== In 1995, according to the results of the [[1995 Belarusian Referendum]], the Russian language was declared the second official language. According to the [[Belarus Census (2009)]], 41.5% of the Belarusian population declared Russian as their [[mother language]] and 70.2% declared Russian "the language spoken at home" (the second language-related question of the Census).
